The derivative of \( x(t) \) is: \[ \frac{dx}{dt} = -A e^{-a t} \left( a \cos(\omega t) + \omega \sin(\omega t) \right) \] Setting the derivative to zero, we get: \[ a \cos(\omega t) + \omega \sin(\omega t) = 0 \] Solving this equation, we find: \[ \tan(\omega t) = -\frac{a}{\omega} \] The solutions to this equation are: \[ \omega t = \arctan\left(-\frac{a}{\omega}\right) + n\pi \quad \text{for integer } n \] This can be rewritten as: \[ t = \frac{1}{\omega} \left( -\arctan\left(\frac{a}{\omega}\right) + n\pi \right) \] The critical points occur at these times.
